Rating: 4
I have made this pesto several times and it is always beyond compare. I just returned from Italy and my husband said that my pesto is still the best he has had. It is critical to use the best ingredients, especially the pine nuts and cheese. Pine nuts can vary quite a bit in quality, those of poor quality being bitter or rancid. Also, use the best quality cheese you can find and grate it yourself. The blanching is critical to keeping the beautiful green color which adds much to the appeal of this dish. Don't squeeze the basil completely dry after blanching and the consistency should be just right. If not, add a bit of water to the processor to thin it out - don't add more oil, which will just make it too oily.

